id: stopwatch/language-change
plugin: manual
_summary: Test to check if stopwatch is working properly after timezone change, without closing Stopwatch
estimated_duration: 600
_description:
    Test to check if stopwatch is working properly after timezone change, without closing Stopwatch
    1. Launch the clock app.
        Clock app opens showing the current local time.
    2. Press stopwatch icon on the top of the screen.
        Stopwatch opens, it is not running. The stopwatch main display shows 00:00:00 000.
    3. Press Start button.
        The main display caunting time. The Start button disappers and the buttons Stop and Lap appear.
    4. Press Lap button.
        New lap row is appering together with header.
    5. Switch to the system settings app. Navigate to Date & Time.
        The field with current timezone should be visible. Remember current timezone setting.
    6. Press current timezone field and change timezone to some different.
        The field Time zone: was changed to selected timezone.
    7. Switch to clock app.
        Stopwatch should appearing instantly. Hours in stopwatch was not changed to different values 
